    <main class="main-content">
        <h1>Jak funguje Biocross</h1>
        <p>Baking a cake is a fun and rewarding experience! Follow these simple steps to create a delicious cake from scratch.</p>
        
        <ol class="steps">
            <li>
                <h2>Gather Ingredients</h2>
                <p>Collect the following ingredients:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>2 cups of flour</li>
                    <li>1 ½ cups of sugar</li>
                    <li>½ cup of butter</li>
                    <li>1 cup of milk</li>
                    <li>3 eggs</li>
                    <li>1 tablespoon of baking powder</li>
                    <li>1 teaspoon of vanilla extract</li></ul>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <h2>Preheat the Oven</h2>
                <p>Set your oven to 350°F (175°C) to preheat while you prepare the batter.</p>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <h2>Mix the Batter</h2>
                <p>In a large bowl, cream the butter and sugar together. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well. Then, stir in the vanilla. In another bowl, combine the flour and baking powder. Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet mixture, alternating with the milk.</p>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <h2>Pour into Pans</h2>
                <p>Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans. Pour the batter evenly into the pans.</p>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <h2>Bake the Cake</h2>
                <p>Place the pans in the preheated oven and bake for 30-35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.</p>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <h2>Cool and Serve</h2>
                <p>Allow the cakes to cool in the pans for 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely before frosting. Enjoy your homemade cake!</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </main>
    
